      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email for Marcus. Here's a sample:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nWe wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and the time you took to prepare for our final interview. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture requirements.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were thoroughly impressed by your qualifications and potential. We appreciate the time and effort you invested in our interview process, and we wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in joining our team and hope that our paths will cross again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nThis email aims to be professional, kind, and firm, while also conveying the reasons for the decision in a clear and respectful manner.",
